a book of the century francie nolan is a young irish-american girl who lived in an ethnic slum in brooklyn around the turn of the century . the story covers her turbulant childhood with little money and alcoholic father . it tells of the menial work her mother did each day as a housekeeper to keep the family together because her father could not hold down a steady job . even though it was tough for the family , francie was kept in school until high school so that she would become educated and not have to wash floors for a living like her mother . also francie was intelligent , idealistic and hard-working . she became very successful as she matured and got her first real job . the story is one of hope that will inspire all who read it . it illustrates the american dream fulfilled through hard work and perserverance